Provides path-safety validation and the canonical mapping between repo-relative source paths and their `.context` mirror files; used throughout `ctx-summarize` to compute where leaf/rollup/intent artifacts live.

Intentionally duplicates ~20 lines of equivalent logic in `ctx-context` (`repo_path`/`chain`) — the two crates are kept independent on purpose, with the duplication tracked in `docs/UNIMPLEMENTED.md` for eventual consolidation into `ctx-core`. Any change to path-safety rules or the `.context` mirror layout here should be checked against that other copy for drift.

`validate_rel(raw: &str) -> Result<(), SummError>` rejects empty paths, absolute paths, and any component that is empty, `.`, `..`, or contains a NUL byte — returns `SummError::PathEscape` rather than panicking. `context_dir_of`, `leaf_ctx`, `rollup_of`, and `intent_of` build the `.context/...` mirror paths (root directory represented as `""`, mapped to `.context` with no trailing segment). `dir_of(src)` returns the parent directory of a path, `""` if `src` is at repo root. `ancestor_dirs(src)` returns every directory prefix from root to `src`'s parent inclusive (e.g. `a/b/c.rs` → `["", "a", "a/b"]`), used to find which rollups a file change can affect — always includes `""` even for root-level files.